The paper deals with scheduling radio resources for vehicle-to-vehicle (V2V) communications, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed solution is based on reinforcement learning (RL), which is a popular machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the state representation and reward function used in the RL algorithm, which are important aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The scheduling problem is formulated as a control problem, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also discusses the wireless channel conditions and resource configuration, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT).
